# ERROR TIPS
### Errors due to lack of fuel
- Ensure that burner mining drills and burners have a sufficient fuel supply before starting operations.
- Regularly check the fuel levels of boilers and steam engines to avoid interruptions.

### Errors due to missing ingredients
- Ensure that stone furnaces have the necessary ingredients to operate.
- Regularly check the inventory of stone furnaces to avoid interruptions.

### Errors due to disconnection from the electric network
- Ensure that electricity groups are properly connected to the electric network.
- Regularly check the connections of electricity groups to avoid interruptions.

### Errors due to empty or full pipe groups
- Ensure that pipe groups are not empty or full before starting operations.
- Regularly check the status of pipe groups to avoid interruptions.
